Question:
What would be the price of the ACA token (Acala Network) on 22/10/2022 (Saturday) at 8:00 UTC? 

Description:
This market aim is to find how the crypto markets will price ACA (Acala Network) tokens in regards to the expected Acala network operations relaunch.

Market mechanics:
Outcome asset tokens (or outcome tokens for short) represent the possible outcomes of a future event. 
If the market resolves to a number within the outcome range, both Long and Short outcome assets will be redeemable at between 0$ and 1$, proportional to where the resolved outcome lies along the range (and totaling 1$). If the market resolves to a number that lies below or above the range, then one of the Long and Short outcome assets would be redeemable to 1$ (and the other would have no value).

Betting Example:
If you want to bet that ACA will be at 0.23$ at market close, then you buy Long at 0.40$ or lower (you predict that Long will redeem for at least 0.40$) and Short at 0.60$ or lower (you predict that Short will redeem for at least 0.60$).

If traders buy "Long" at 0.40$ or lower, they bet that ACA token price will at least be at:
5 + (0.4 x 45) = 23 / 100 (scale) = 0.23$ at the the market close.

If traders buy "Short" at 0.60$ or lower, they bet that ACA token price will at least be at:
